History of Lean Design History of Lean Design
In 1982 Sandy Munro met Dr E. Deming and his ideas regarding reducing variation to increase quality resonated with Sandy; becoming a zealot in reducing variation and analyzing how to eliminate waste in the design phase. Read more »

